# Cursor Rules — Chaos UI

You are working on Chaos UI (`@chaos_team/chaos-ui`), an enterprise React component library.

## Tech Stack
- React 19, Next.js 16, TypeScript 5.9, Tailwind CSS 4
- @base-ui/react for primitives, cva for variants, tailwind-merge for class merging
- Storybook 10 for component development
- Vitest + Testing Library for tests

## Code Style
- Named exports only (no default exports)
- `@/` import alias for project-local source
- `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for className merging
- `data-slot` attribute on root element of each component
- JSDoc comments on all exports: `@component`, `@category`, `@since`, `@example`

## Component Structure
```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
import { cva, type VariantProps } from "class-variance-authority"

const componentVariants = cva("base", { variants: {}, defaultVariants: {} })

function Component({ className, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"div"> & VariantProps<typeof componentVariants>) {
  return <div data-slot="component" className={cn(componentVariants({ className }))} {...props} />
}

export { Component, componentVariants }
```

## File Locations
- UI primitives: `components/ui/`
- Business components: `components/business/`
- Layout components: `components/layout/`
- Hooks: `hooks/`
- Lib utils: `lib/`
- Stories: `src/`

## Verification
- `npm run check` (typecheck + lint + css lint + dep check)
- `npm test` (vitest)
- `npm run build-storybook`
- `npm run build:pkg`
